race.comment: NO FOOLING (3) looks the one to beat with a run under the belt. He's a lightly raced 4yo who was just found wanting for fitness first up with 61kg here having promised plenty in his initial campaign. Stays at 1000m but draws well again and should go close. INTEREST POINT (1) is coming off a dominant win at Ballarat over this trip last time out, scoring by 2.5 lengths. He's handy on his day and a repeat of that performance will go close again. SUPERNIMA (2) resumes with an imposing record on her home track, winning two of three and running second in the other. 1000m is short of his best but he's got the ability to be running well. LATIN BOSS (9) resumes having shown good 2yo ability. He's jumped out well and has claims fresh.
